# gen214, Italian probe: teach a new ask_name form through the Italian label "il mio
# nome" ("impara \"…\" per il mio nome"). The generic teach path matches the label
# against the RAW (non-canonical) turn, so EN and IT labels both route through one
# handler — the bilingual ratchet. The stored form is the canonicalized span, so a later
# turn recalls the name through it.
> mi chiamo Bob
< Nice to meet you, Bob!
> impara "come mi chiami" per il mio nome
< Got it - I'll take "come mi chiami" as a way to il mio nome now.
> come mi chiami
< Your name is Bob.
